Remove this attribute from your `&lt;TextView&gt;` tag:

&gt;     android:layerType=&quot;software&quot;

Hardware acceleration is required for views to draw outside of their bounds. Note that padding doesn&#39;t help here because view contents are clipped by padding as well.

You can use another method to make it blurred. Additional benefit is that it can be used on other View types and ViewGroups.

    view.setRenderEffect(RenderEffect.createBlurEffect(15f, 15f, Shader.TileMode.CLAMP))

It can be drawn on padding

    android:clipToPadding=&quot;false&quot;
    android:padding=&quot;5dp&quot;

